78ac06b3-468d-4818-926e-015006c92c7f.do_description: To make the output, you have to....copy the input. If two blocks across from each other are the same color, fill in the rest of that horizontal row with that color. Don't do anything with the blocks across from each other that are different colors
78ac06b3-468d-4818-926e-015006c92c7f.grid_description: The output grid size...stays the same size as the input.
78ac06b3-468d-4818-926e-015006c92c7f.see_description: In the input, you should see...single pixels of different colors in two horizontal lines along the left and right sides of the grid.

c9032fa5-092d-4e11-90fd-e3fe497925a9.do_description: To make the output, you have to....one black row at the top, then add a row of colored blocks, any color, all the way through and then fill in one or two of the colored rows with the first block in that row color
c9032fa5-092d-4e11-90fd-e3fe497925a9.see_description: In the input, you should see...rows of colored blocks with a black row in between
